Questions:
Which of the following procedures is considered experimental in the context of this study?
A) Laparoscopic resection of large organs such as kidneys;
B) Removal of resected organ samples through an additional abdominal incision;
C) Transvaginal extraction of laparoscopically-excised kidney specimen;
D) Gynecological examination prior to surgery.

Correct answer: C

If you choose not to participate in the study, what is the standard procedure for removing the resected organ after laparoscopic surgery?
A) The organ is left in place and not removed; 
B) The organ is removed through a natural orifice without any incision;
C) The organ is removed through an additional abdominal incision of 5-7 cm;
D) The organ is dissolved using medication and absorbed by the body.

Correct answer: C

Who is authorized to access your medical records for the purpose of verifying clinical trial procedures and data according to the new consent form?
A) Only the research team conducting the study;
B) Monitoring personnel, inspectors, review committees, and the Minister of Food and Drug Safety;
C) Family members of the participant;
D) All hospital staff regardless of their involvement in the study.

Correct answer: B
